  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (49601)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Formation of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir with Legislature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49601&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On and from the`
  line `appointed day, there shall be formed a new Union territory to be known as the Union territory of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir comprising the territories of the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir other than`
  line `those specified in section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (49602)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Governor of existing State of Jammu and Kashmir to be common Lieutenant Governor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49602&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, the Governor of the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir shall be the`
  line `Lieutenant Governor for the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, and Union territory of Ladakh for`
  line `such period as may be determined by the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (49603)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Amendment of First Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49603&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in the`
  line `First Schedule to the Constitution, under the heading--- "I. THE STATES",---`
  line
  line `(a) entry 15 shall be deleted.`
  line
  line `(b) entries from 16 to 29 shall be renumbered as 15 to 28.`
  line
  line `(c) under the heading --- "II. UNION TERRITORIES",---`
  line
  line `after entry 7, the following entries shall be inserted, namely:---`
  line
  line `"8. Jammu and Kashmir: The territories specified in section 4 of the Jammu and Kashmir`
  line `Reorganisation Act, 2019".`
  line
  line `"9. Ladakh: The territories specified in section 3 of the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation`
  line `Act, 2019".`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (49604)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Saving powers of the Government of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49604&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line Nothing
  line `in the foregoing provisions of this Part shall be deemed to affect the power of the Government of`
  line `successor Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir to alter, after the appointed day, the name, area or`
  line `boundaries of any district or other territorial division in that Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (49605)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Amendment of Fourth Schedule to Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49605&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in the`
  line `Fourth Schedule to the Constitution, in the Table,---`
  line
  line `(a) entry 21 shall be deleted;`
  line
  line `(b) entries 22 to 31 shall be renumbered as entries 21 to 30, respectively;`
  line
  line `(c) after entry 30, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:---`
  line
  line `"31. Jammu and Kashmir ..................................................4".`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (49606)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Allocation of sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49606&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, four sitting members of`
  line `the Council of States representing the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir shall be deemed to have`
  line `been elected to fill the seats allotted to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, as specified in the First`
  line `Schedule to this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of such sitting members shall remain unaltered.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (49607)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Representation in House of the People.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49607&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, there shall be`
  line `allocated five seats to the successor Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and one seat to Union`
  line `territory of Ladakh, in the House of the People, and the First Schedule to the Representation of the`
  line `People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950) shall be deemed to be amended accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (49608)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Delimitation of Parliamentary Constituencies Order, 1976.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49608&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed`
  line `day, the Delimitation of Parliamentary Constituencies Order, 1976 shall stand amended as directed in the`
  line `Second Schedule of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Election Commission may conduct the elections to the House of the People for the Union`
  line `territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh as per the allocation of seats specified`
  line `in the Delimitation of Parliamentary Constituencies Order, 1976 as amended by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (49609)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Provision as to sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49609&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every sitting member of the House of the People`
  line `representing a constituency which, on the appointed day by virtue of the provisions of section 10,`
  line `stands allotted, with or without alteration of boundaries, to the successor Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir or Union territory of Ladakh, as the case may be, shall be deemed to have been elected`
  line `to the House of the People by that constituency as so allotted.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of such sitting members shall remain unaltered.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (49610)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Applicability of article 239A of Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 2021, s. 2 (w.e.f. 7-1-2021)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49610&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, the provisions`
  line `contained in article 239A, ^1[or any other article containing reference to elected members of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the State] which are applicable to "Union territory of Puducherry", shall also`
  line `apply to the "Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir".`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (49611)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Legislative Assembly for the Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir and its composition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49611&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be an Administrator appointed under article 239 of the Constitution of`
  line `India for the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and shall be designated as Lieutenant Governor of`
  line `the said Union territory.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be a Legislative Assembly for the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  line
  line `(3) The total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir to be filled by persons chosen by direct election shall be 107.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Provided that subject to the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 60, on and from the date of commencement of the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Amendment) Act, 2023, the provisions of this sub-section shall have effect as if for the figures "107", the figures "114" had been substituted.]`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), until the area of the Union territory of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir under the occupation of Pakistan ceases to be so occupied and the people`
  line `residing in that area elect their representatives---`
  line
  line `(a) twenty four seats in the Legislative Assembly of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir`
  line `shall remain vacant and shall not be taken into account for reckoning the total membership of the`
  line `Assembly; and`
  line
  line `(b) the said area and seats shall be excluded in delimiting the territorial constituencies as`
  line `provided under PART V of this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) On and from the appointed day, the Delimitation of Assembly Constituencies Order, 1995,`
  line `as applicable to Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, shall stand amended as directed in the Third`
  line `Schedule of this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) Seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes in the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  line
  line `(7) The number of seats reserved for the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir under sub-section (6) shall bear,`
  line `as nearly as may be, the same proportion to the total number of seats in the Assembly as the`
  line `population of the Scheduled Castes in the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir or of the`
  line `Scheduled Tribes in the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, in respect of which seats are so`
  line `reserved, bears to the total population of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  line
  line `Explanation:--- In this sub-section, the expression population means the population as`
  line `ascertained at the last preceding census of which the relevant figures have been published:`
  line
  line `Provided that the reference in this Explanation to the last preceding census of which the relevant`
  line `figures have been published shall, until the relevant figures for the first census taken after the year`
  line `2026 have been published, be construed as a reference to the 2011 census.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything in sub-section (6), the reservation of seats for the Scheduled`
  line `Castes or Scheduled Tribes in the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir shall cease to have effect on the same date on which the reservation of seats for the`
  line `Scheduled Castes or the Scheduled Tribes in the House of the People shall cease to have effect`
  line `under article 334 of the Constitution of India.`
  line
  line `(9) In the Second Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950), under the`
  line `heading :--- "I. THE STATES:"---`
  line
  line `"(a) entry 10 shall be deleted".`
  line
  line `"(b) entries 11 to 29 shall be renumbered as 10 to 28".`
  line
  line `^2 [ (10) In the Second Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950), under the sub-heading "II. UNION TERRITORIES", against serial number 3 relating to "Jammu and Kashmir", for the entries under columns 2 to 7, the following entries shall respectively be substituted, namely:---`
  line
  line `12 34 567`
  line
  line `"3. Jammu and Kashmir90799079". ].`
  line
  line `(11) The provisions of articles 324 to 327 and 329 of the Constitution of India, shall apply in relation to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, the Legislative Assembly and the members thereof as they apply, in relation to a State, the Legislative Assembly of a State and the members thereof respectively; and any reference in articles 326 and 329 to "appropriate Legislature" shall be deemed to be a`
  line `reference to Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 2023, s. 2 (w.e.f. 26-12-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for sub-section (10) (w.e.f. 26-12-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (49612)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Representation of women.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49612&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in sub-section (3) of section 14 the`
  line `Lieutenant Governor of the successor Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir may nominate two`
  line `members to the Legislative Assembly to give representation to women, if in his opinion, women are`
  line `not adequately represented in the Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (89198)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 16
  title `Nomination of Kashmiri Migrants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 2023, s. 3 (w.e.f. 26-12-2023)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=89198&sectionno=15A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 [15A. Nomination of Kashmiri Migrants.—Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section`
  line `(3) of section 14, the Lieutenant Governor of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir may nominate`
  line `not more than two members, one of whom shall be a woman, from the community of Kashmiri`
  line `Migrants, to the Jammu and Kashmir Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, the term "Migran" shall have the same meaning as`
  line `assigned to it in clause (e) of section 2 of the Jammu and Kashmir Migrant Immovable Property`
  line `(Preservation, Protection and Restraint on Distress Sales) Act, 1997 (Jammu and Kashmir Act XVI of`
  line `1997).]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_b:
  sectionId (89199)
  sectionNo 15B
  orderNo 17
  title `Nomination of displaced persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 2023, s. 3 (w.e.f. 26-12-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=89199&sectionno=15B&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[15B. Nomination of displaced persons. —Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 14, the Lieutenant Governor of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir may nominate`
  line `one member from displaced persons from Pakistan occupied Jammu and Kashmir to the Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, the term "displaced person" means any person,`
  line `who, on account of the setting up of the dominions of India and Pakistan, or on account of civil`
  line `disturbances or fear of such disturbances in any area of the then State of Jammu and Kashmir presently`
  line `under occupation of Pakistan, during the years 1947-48, 1965 and 1971, had left or had been displaced`
  line `due to such disturbances from his place of residence in such area and who has been subsequently`
  line `residing outside such area and also includes successors-in-interest of any such person.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (49613)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Qualification for membership of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49613&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `A person shall not be qualified to`
  line `be chosen to fill a seat in the Legislative Assembly unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) is a citizen of India and makes and subscribes before some person authorised in that`
  line `behalf by the Election Commission an oath or affirmation according to the form set out for the`
  line `purpose in the Fourth Schedule of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) is not less than twenty-five years of age; and`
  line
  line `(c) possesses such other qualifications as may be prescribed in that behalf by or under any`
  line `law made by the Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (49614)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Duration of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49614&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Legislative Assembly, unless sooner dissolved, shall`
  line `continue for five years from the date appointed for its first meeting and no longer, and the expiration of`
  line `the said period of five years shall operate as a dissolution of the Legislative Assembly:`
  line
  line `Provided that the said period may, while a Proclamation of Emergency issued under clause (1) of`
  line `article 352 is in operation, be extended by the President by order for a period not exceeding one year at a`
  line `time and not extending in any case beyond a period of six months after the Proclamation has ceased to`
  line operate.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (49615)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Sessions of Legislative Assembly, prorogation and dissolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49615&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Lieutenant`
  line `Governor shall, from time to time, summon the Legislative Assembly to meet at such time and place as`
  line `he thinks fit, but six months shall not intervene between its last sitting in one session and the date appointed for`
  line `its first sitting in the next session.`
  line
  line `(2) The Lieutenant Governor may, from time to time,---`
  line
  line `(a) prorogue the House;br`
  line
  line `(b) dissolve the Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (49616)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Speaker and Deputy Speaker of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49616&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Legislative Assembly`
  line `shall, as soon as may be, choose two members of the Assembly to be respectively Speaker and Deputy`
  line `Speaker thereof and, so often as the office of Speaker or Deputy Speaker becomes vacant, the Assembly`
  line `shall choose another member to be Speaker or Deputy Speaker, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) A member holding office as Speaker or Deputy Speaker of the Assembly---`
  line
  line `(a) shall vacate his office if he ceases to be a member of the Assembly;`
  line
  line `(b) may at any time by writing under his hand addressed, if such member is the Speaker, to the`
  line `Deputy Speaker, and if such member is the Deputy Speaker, to the Speaker, resign his office;`
  line
  line `(c) may be removed from his office by a resolution of the Assembly passed by a majority of all the`
  line `then members of the Assembly:`
  line
  line `Provided that no resolution for the purpose of clause (c) shall be moved unless at least fourteen`
  line `days' notice has been given of the intention to move the resolution:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, whenever the Assembly is dissolved, the Speaker shall not vacate his office`
  line `until immediately before the first meeting of the Assembly after the dissolution.`
  line
  line `(3) While the office of Speaker is vacant, the duties of the office shall be performed by the Deputy`
  line `Speaker or, if the office of Deputy Speaker is also vacant, by such member of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly as may be determined by the rules of procedure of the Assembly.`
  line
  line `(4) During the absence of the Speaker from any sitting of the Legislative Assembly, the Deputy`
  line `Speaker, or, if he is also absent, such person as may be determined by the rules of procedure of the`
  line `Assembly, or, if no such person is present, such other person as may be determined by the Legislative`
  line `Assembly, shall act as Speaker.`
  line
  line `(5) There shall be paid to the Speaker and the Deputy Speaker of the Legislative Assembly, such`
  line `salaries and allowances as may respectively be fixed by the Legislative Assembly of the Union`
  line `territory of Jammu and Kashmir by law and, until provision in that behalf is so made, such salaries`
  line `and allowances as the Lieutenant Governor may, by order determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (49701)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Speaker or Deputy Speaker not to preside while a resolution for his removal from office is under consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49701&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any sitting of the Legislative Assembly, while any resolution for the`
  line `removal of the Speaker from his office is under consideration, the Speaker, or while any resolution for`
  line `the removal of the Deputy Speaker, from his office is under consideration, the Deputy Speaker, shall`
  line `not, though he is present, preside, and the provisions of sub-section (4) of section 19 shall apply in`
  line `relation to every such sitting as they apply in relation to a sitting from which the Speaker or, as the`
  line `case may be, the Deputy Speaker, is absent.`
  line
  line `(2) The Speaker shall have the right to speak in, and otherwise to take part in the proceedings of,`
  line `the Legislative Assembly while any resolution for his removal from office is under consideration in`
  line `the Assembly and shall, notwithstanding anything in section 25, be entitled to vote only in the first`
  line `instance on such resolution or on any other matter during such proceedings but not in the case of an`
  line `equality of votes.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (49618)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Special address by Lieutenant Governor to Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49618&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) At the`
  line `commencement of the first session after each general election to the Legislative Assembly and at the`
  line `commencement of the first session of each year, the Lieutenant Governor shall address the Legislative`
  line `Assembly, and shall inform the Legislative Assembly of the causes of its summons.`
  line
  line `(2) Provision shall be made by the rules regulating the procedure of the Legislative Assembly for`
  line `the allotment of time for the discussion of matters referred to in such address.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (49619)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title `Rights of Ministers and Advocate General as respects Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49619&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line Every
  line `Minister and the Advocate-General for the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir shall have the right`
  line `to speak in, and otherwise to take part in the proceedings of, the Legislative Assembly, and to speak`
  line `in, and otherwise to take part in the proceedings of, any committee of the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `which he may be named a member, but shall not by virtue of this section be entitled to vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (49620)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 25
  title `Rights of Lieutenant Governor to address and send messages to the Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49620&sectionno=23&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Lieutenant Governor may address the Legislative Assembly and may for that purpose`
  line `require the attendance of members.`
  line
  line `(2) The Lieutenant Governor may also send messages to the Legislative Assembly whether with`
  line `respect to a Bill then pending in the Legislative Assembly or otherwise, and when a message so sent,`
  line `the Legislative Assembly shall with all convenient despatch consider any matter required by the`
  line `message to be taken into consideration.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (49621)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title `Oath or affirmation by members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49621&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Legislative Assembly shall, before`
  line `taking his seat, make and subscribe before the Lieutenant Governor of the said Union territory, or`
  line `some person appointed in that behalf by him, an oath or affirmation according to the form set out for`
  line `the purpose in the Fourth Schedule of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (49622)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title `Voting in Assembly, power of Assembly to act notwithstanding vacancies and quorum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49622&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, all questions at any sitting of the Legislative Assembly`
  line `shall be determined by a majority of votes of the members present and voting, other than the Speaker`
  line `or person acting as such.`
  line
  line `(2) The Speaker, or person acting as such, shall not vote in the first instance, but shall have and`
  line `exercise a casting vote in the case of an equality of votes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Legislative Assembly shall have power to act notwithstanding any vacancy in the`
  line `membership thereof, and any proceedings in the Legislative Assembly shall be valid notwithstanding`
  line `that it is discovered subsequently that some person who was not entitled so to do, sat or voted or`
  line `otherwise took part in the proceedings.`
  line
  line `(4) The quorum to constitute a meeting of the Legislative Assembly shall be ten members or onetenth of the total number of members of the Legislative Assembly, which ever is greater.`
  line
  line `(5) If at any time during a meeting of the Legislative Assembly there is no quorum, it shall be the`
  line `duty of the Speaker, or person acting as such, either to adjourn the Legislative Assembly or to suspend`
  line `the meeting until there is a quorum.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (49623)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Vacation of seats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49623&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall be a member both of Parliament and of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly, and if a person is chosen a member both of Parliament and of such Assembly, then, at the`
  line `expiration of such period as may be specified in the rules made by the President, that person's seat in`
  line `Parliament shall become vacant, unless he has previously resigned his seat in the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the said Union territory.`
  line
  line `(2) If a member of the Legislative Assembly--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes subject to any of disqualification mentioned in section 27 or section 28 for`
  line `membership of the Legislative Assembly; or`
  line
  line `(b) resigns his seat by writing under his hand addressed to the Speaker, and his resignation is`
  line `accepted by the Speaker,`
  line
  line `his seat shall thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line `(3) If for a period of sixty days a member of the Legislative Assembly is without permission of the`
  line `Assembly absent from all meetings thereof, the Assembly may declare his seat vacant:`
  line
  line `Provided that in computing the said period of sixty days, no account shall be taken of any`
  line `period during which the Assembly is prorogued or is adjourned for more than four consecutive`
  line days.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (49624)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title `Disqualifications for membership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49624&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be disqualified for being chosen as,`
  line `and for being, a member of the Legislative Assembly--`
  line
  line `(a) if he holds any office of profit under the Government of India or the Government of any`
  line `State or the Government of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir or the Government or`
  line `administration of any other Union territory or other than an office declared by law made by`
  line `Parliament or by the Legislative Assembly not to disqualify its holder; or`
  line
  line `(b) if he is for the time being disqualified for being chosen as, and for being, a member of either`
  line `House of Parliament under the provisions of sub-clause (b), sub-clause (c) or sub-clause (d) of`
  line `clause (1) of article 102 or of any law made in pursuance of that article.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, a person shall not be deemed to hold an office of profit under`
  line `the Government of India or the Government of any State or the Government of Union territory of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir or the Government of any other Union territory by reason only that he is a`
  line `Minister either for the Union or for such State or Union territory.`
  line
  line `(3) If any question arises as to whether a member of the Legislative Assembly becomes subject to`
  line `any of disqualification under the provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2), the question shall be referred`
  line `for the decision of the Lieutenant Governor and his decision shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) Before giving any decision on any such question, the Lieutenant Governor shall obtain the`
  line `opinion of the Election Commission and shall act according to such opinion.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (49625)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Disqualification on ground of defection for being a member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49625&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the Tenth`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution shall, subject to the necessary modifications (including modifications for construing references therein to the Legislative Assembly of a State, article 188, article 194 and article`
  line `212 as references, respectively, to the Legislative Assembly of Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir, as the case may be, section 24, section 30 and section 50 of this Act), apply to and in`
  line `relation to the members of the Legislative Assembly of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir as they`
  line `apply to and in relation to the members of the Legislative Assembly of a State, and accordingly,--`
  line
  line `(a) the said Tenth Schedule as so modified shall be deemed to form part of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) a person shall be disqualified for being a member of the Legislative Assembly if he is so`
  line `disqualified under the said Tenth Schedule as so modified.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (49702)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Penalty for sitting and voting before making oath or affirmation or when not qualified or when disqualified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49702&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `If a person sits or votes as a member of the Legislative Assembly before he has`
  line `complied with the requirements of section 24 or when he knows that he is not qualified or that he is`
  line `disqualified for membership thereof, or that he is prohibited from doing so by the provisions of any`
  line `law made by Parliament or the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, he`
  line `shall be liable in respect of each day on which he so sits or votes to a penalty of five hundred rupees to`
  line `be recovered as a debt due to the said Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (49627)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Powers, privileges, etc., of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49627&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and to the`
  line `rules and standing orders regulating the procedure of the Legislative Assembly, there shall be freedom`
  line `of speech in the Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `(2) No member of the Legislative Assembly shall be liable to any proceedings in any court in`
  line `respect of anything said or any vote given by him in the Assembly or any committee thereof, and no`
  line `person shall be so liable in respect of the publication by or under the authority of such Assembly of`
  line `any report, paper, votes or proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) In other respects, the powers, privileges and immunities of the Legislative Assembly and of the`
  line `members and the committees thereof shall be such as are for the time being enjoyed by the House of`
  line `the People and its members and committees.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-sections (1), (2) and (3) shall apply in relation to persons who by virtue`
  line `of this Act have the right to speak in, and otherwise to take part in the proceedings of, the Legislative`
  line `Assembly or any committee thereof as they apply in relation to members of the Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (49628)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title `Salaries and allowances of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49628&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Members of the Legislative Assembly shall be`
  line `entitled to receive such salaries and allowances as may from time to time be determined by the`
  line `Legislative Assembly by law and, until provision in that behalf is so made, such salaries and`
  line `allowances as the Lieutenant Governor may, by order determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (49629)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Extent of legislative power.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49629&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Legislative`
  line `Assembly may make laws for the whole or any part of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir`
  line `with respect to any of the matters enumerated in the State List except the subjects mentioned at entries`
  line `1 and 2, namely "Public Order" and "Police" respectively or the Concurrent List in the Seventh`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution of India in so far as any such matter is applicable in relation to the Union`
  line territories.
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall derogate from the powers conferred on Parliament by the`
  line `Constitution to make laws with respect to any matter for the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir or`
  line `any part thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (49630)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title `Exemption of property of the Union from taxation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49630&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The property of the Union shall, save`
  line `in so far as Parliament may by law otherwise provide, be exempted from all taxes imposed by or`
  line `under any law made by the Legislative Assembly or by or under any other law in force in the Union`
  line `territory of Jammu and Kashmir:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall, until Parliament by law otherwise provides, prevent any`
  line `authority within the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir from levying any tax on any property of`
  line `the Union to which such property was immediately before the commencement of the Constitution liable or treated as liable, so long as that tax continues to be levied in that Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (49631)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 36
  title `Restrictions on laws passed by Legislative Assembly with respect to certain matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49631&sectionno=34&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of article 286, article 287 and article 288 shall apply in relation to any law passed`
  line `by the Legislative Assembly with respect to any of the matters referred to in those articles as they`
  line `apply in relation to any law passed by the Legislature of a State with respect to those matters.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of article 304 shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to any`
  line `law passed by the Legislative Assembly with respect to any of the matters referred to in that article as`
  line `they apply in relation to any law passed by the Legislature of a State with respect to those matters.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (49703)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 37
  title `Inconsistency between laws made by Parliament and laws made by Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49703&sectionno=35&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `If any provision of a law made by the Legislative Assembly with respect to matters`
  line `enumerated in the State List, in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution is repugnant to any provision`
  line `of a law made by Parliament with respect to that matter, whether passed before or after the law made`
  line `by the Legislative Assembly, or, if any provision of a law made by the Legislative Assembly with`
  line `respect to any matter enumerated in the Concurrent List in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution is`
  line `repugnant to any provision of any earlier law, other than a law made by the Legislative Assembly,`
  line `with respect to that matter, then, in either case, the law made by Parliament, or, as the case may be,`
  line `such earlier law shall prevail and the law made by the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory`
  line `shall, to the extent of the repugnancy, be void:`
  line
  line `Provided that if such law made by the Legislative Assembly has been reserved for the`
  line `consideration of the President and has received his assent, such law shall prevail in the Union`
  line `territory of Jammu and Kashmir:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this section shall prevent Parliament from enacting at any time`
  line `any law with respect to the same matter including a law adding to, amending, varying or repealing`
  line `the law so made by the Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (49633)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 38
  title `Special provisions as to financial Bills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49633&sectionno=36&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Bill or amendment shall not be introduced`
  line `into, or moved in, the Legislative Assembly except on the recommendation of the Lieutenant`
  line `Governor, if such Bill or Amendment makes provision for any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the imposition, abolition, remission, alteration or regulation of any tax;`
  line
  line `(b) the amendment of the law with respect to any financial obligations undertaken or to be`
  line `undertaken by the Government of the Union territory;`
  line
  line `(c) the appropriation of moneys out of the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory;`
  line
  line `(d) the declaring of any expenditure to be expenditure charged on the Consolidated Fund of the`
  line `Union territory or the increasing of the amount of any such expenditure;`
  line
  line `(e) the receipt of money on account of the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory or the`
  line `public account of the Union territory or the custody or issue of such money or the audit of the`
  line `account of the Union territory:`
  line
  line `Provided that no recommendation shall be required under this sub-section for the moving of an`
  line `amendment making provision for the reduction or abolition of any tax.`
  line
  line `(2) A Bill or Amendment shall not be deemed to make provision for any of the matters aforesaid`
  line `by reason only that it provides for the imposition of fines or other pecuniary penalties, or for the`
  line `demand or payment of fees for licences or fees for services rendered, or by reason that it provides for`
  line `the imposition, abolition, remission, alteration or regulation of any tax by any local authority or body`
  line `for local purposes.`
  line
  line `(3) A Bill which, if enacted and brought into operation, would involve expenditure from the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of Union territory shall not be passed by the Legislative Assembly of the Union`
  line `territory unless the Lieutenant Governor has recommended to the Assembly, the consideration of the`
  line Bill.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (49634)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 39
  title `Procedure as to lapsing of Bills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49634&sectionno=37&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Bill pending in the Legislative Assembly shall not`
  line `lapse by reason of the prorogation of the Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `(2) A Bill which is pending in the Legislative Assembly shall lapse on dissolution of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (49635)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 40
  title `Assent to Bills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49635&sectionno=38&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `When a Bill has been passed by the Legislative Assembly, it shall be`
  line `presented to the Lieutenant Governor and the Lieutenant Governor shall declare either that he assents`
  line `to the Bill or that he withholds assent therefrom or that he reserves the Bill for the consideration of the`
  line `President:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Lieutenant Governor may, as soon as possible after the presentation of the Bill to`
  line `him for assent, return the Bill if it is not a Money Bill together with a message requesting that the`
  line `Assembly will reconsider the Bill or any specified provisions thereof, and, in particular, will consider`
  line `the desirability of introducing any such amendments as he may recommend in his message and, when`
  line `a Bill is so returned, the Assembly will reconsider the Bill accordingly, and if the Bill is passed again`
  line `with or without amendment and presented to the Lieutenant Governor for assent, the Lieutenant`
  line `Governor shall declare either that he assents to the Bill or that he reserves the Bill for the`
  line `consideration of the President:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Lieutenant Governor shall not assent to, but shall reserve for the`
  line `consideration of the President, any Bill which,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the opinion of the Lieutenant Governor would, if it became law, so derogate from the`
  line `powers of the High Court as to endanger the position which that Court is, by the Constitution,`
  line `designed to fill; or`
  line
  line `(b) relates to any of the matters specified in clause (1) of article 31A; or`
  line
  line `(c) the President may, by order, direct to be reserved for his consideration.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section and section 39, a Bill shall be deemed to be a`
  line `Money Bill if it contains only provisions dealing with all or any of the matters specified in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 36 or any matter incidental to any of those matters and, in either case,`
  line `there is endorsed thereon the certificate of the Speaker of the Legislative Assembly signed by him`
  line `that it is a Money Bill.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (49636)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 41
  title `Bills reserved for consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49636&sectionno=39&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `When a Bill is reserved by Lieutenant Governor for the`
  line `consideration of the President, the President shall declare either that he assents to the Bill or that he`
  line `withholds assent therefrom:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Bill is not a Money Bill, the President may direct the Lieutenant Governor`
  line `to return the Bill to the Legislative Assembly together with such a message as is mentioned in the first`
  line `proviso to section 38 and, when a Bill is so returned, the Assembly shall reconsider it accordingly`
  line `within a period of six months from the date of receipt of such message and, if it is again passed by the`
  line `Assembly with or without amendment, it shall be presented again to the President for his`
  line consideration.
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (49637)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 42
  title `Requirements as to sanction and recommendations to be regarded as matters of procedure only.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49637&sectionno=40&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `No Act of the Legislative Assembly and no provision in any such Act, shall be`
  line `invalid by reason only that some previous sanction or recommendation required by this Act was not`
  line `given, if assent to that Act was given by the Lieutenant Governor, or, on being reserved by the`
  line `Lieutenant Governor for the consideration of the President, by the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (49638)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 43
  title `Annual financial statement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49638&sectionno=41&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Lieutenant Governor shall in respect of every financial`
  line `year cause to be laid before the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, a`
  line `statement of the estimated receipts and expenditure of the Union territory for that year, in this Part`
  line `referred to as the “annual financial statement”.`
  line
  line `(2) The estimates of expenditure embodied in the annual financial statement shall show separately--`
  line
  line `(a) the sums required to meet expenditure described by this Act as expenditure charged upon`
  line `the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, and`
  line
  line `(b) the sums required to meet other expenditure proposed to be made from the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir; and shall distinguish expenditure on revenue`
  line `account from other expenditure.`
  line
  line `(3) The following expenditure shall be expenditure charged on the Consolidated Fund of the`
  line `Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir:--`
  line
  line `(a) the emoluments and allowances of the Lieutenant Governor and other expenditure relating`
  line `to his office;`
  line
  line `(b) the charges payable in respect of loans advanced to the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir from the Consolidated Fund of India including interest, sinking fund charges and`
  line `redemption charges, and other expenditure connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(c) the salaries and allowances of the Speaker and the Deputy Speaker of the Legislative`
  line Assembly;
  line
  line `(d) expenditure in respect of the salaries and allowances of Judges of High Court of Jammu and`
  line Kashmir;
  line
  line `(e) any sums required to satisfy any judgment, decree or award of any court or arbitral tribunal;`
  line
  line `(f) expenditure incurred by the Lieutenant Governor in the discharge of his special`
  line responsibility;
  line
  line `(g) any other expenditure declared by the Constitution or by law made by Parliament or by the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir to be so charged.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (49639)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 44
  title `Procedure in Legislative Assembly with respect to estimates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49639&sectionno=42&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) So much of the estimates`
  line `as relates to expenditure charged upon the Consolidated Fund of Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir shall not be submitted to the vote of the Legislative Assembly, but nothing in this`
  line `sub-section shall be construed as preventing the discussion in the Legislative Assembly of any of`
  line `those estimates.`
  line
  line `(2) So much of the said estimates as relates to other expenditure shall be submitted in the form of`
  line `demands for grants to the Legislative Assembly, and the Legislative Assembly shall have power to`
  line `assent, or to refuse to assent, to any demand, or to assent to any demand subject to a reduction of the`
  line `amount specified therein.`
  line
  line `(3) No demand for a grant shall be made except on the recommendation of the Lieutenant`
  line Governor.
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (49640)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 45
  title `Appropriation Bills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49640&sectionno=43&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the grants under section 42 have been`
  line `made by the Legislative Assembly, there shall be introduced a Bill to provide for the appropriation out`
  line `of the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of all moneys required to meet--`
  line
  line `(a) the grants so made by the Legislative Assembly, and`
  line
  line `(b) the expenditure charged on the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir but not exceeding in any case the amount shown in the statement previously laid before`
  line `the Assembly.`
  line
  line `(2) No amendment shall be proposed to any such Bill in the Legislative Assembly which will have`
  line `the effect of varying the amount or altering the destination of any grant so made or of varying the`
  line `amount of any expenditure charged on the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir and the decision of the person presiding as to whether an amendment is inadmissible under`
  line `this sub-section shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, no money shall be withdrawn from the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of the Union territory except under appropriation made by law passed in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (49641)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 46
  title `Supplementary, additional or excess grants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49641&sectionno=44&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Lieutenant Governor shall---`
  line
  line `(a) if the amount authorised by any law made in accordance with the provisions of section 43 to`
  line `be expended for a particular service for the current financial year is found to be insufficient for the`
  line `purposes of that year or when a need has arisen during the current financial year for supplementary`
  line `or additional expenditure upon some new service not contemplated in the annual financial`
  line `statement for that year, or`
  line
  line `(b) if any money has been spent on any service during a financial year in excess of the amount`
  line `granted for that service and for that year,`
  line
  line `cause to be laid before the Legislative Assembly, another statement showing the estimated amount of`
  line `that expenditure or cause to be presented to the Legislative Assembly with such previous approval a`
  line `demand for such excess, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sections 41, 42 and 43 shall have effect in relation to any such statement and`
  line `expenditure or demand and also to any law to be made authorising the appropriation of moneys out of`
  line `the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir to meet such expenditure or the`
  line `grant in respect of such demand as they have effect in relation to the annual financial statement and`
  line `the expenditure mentioned therein or to a demand for a grant and the law to be made for the`
  line `authorisation of appropriation of moneys out of the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir to meet such expenditure or grant.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (49642)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 47
  title `Votes on account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49642&sectionno=45&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in the foregoing provisions of this Part, the`
  line `Legislative Assembly shall have power to make any grant in advance in respect of the estimated`
  line `expenditure for a part of any financial year pending the completion of the procedure prescribed in`
  line `section 42 for the voting of such grant and the passing of the law in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `section 43 in relation to that expenditure and the Legislative Assembly shall have power to authorise`
  line `by law the withdrawal of moneys from the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir for the purposes for which the said grant is made.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sections 42 and 43 shall have effect in relation to the making of any grant`
  line `under sub-section (1) or to any law to be made under that sub-section as they have effect in relation to`
  line `the making of a grant with regard to any expenditure mentioned in the annual financial statement and`
  line `the law to be made for the authorisation of appropriation of moneys out of the Consolidated Fund of`
  line `the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir to meet such expenditure.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (49643)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 48
  title `Rules of procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49643&sectionno=46&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Legislative Assembly may make rules for regulating, subject to`
  line `the provisions of this Act, its procedure and the conduct of its business:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Lieutenant Governor shall, after consultation with the Speaker of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly, make rules---`
  line
  line `(a) for securing the timely completion of financial business;`
  line
  line `(b) for regulating the procedure of, and the conduct of business in, the Legislative Assembly in`
  line `relation to any financial matter or to any Bill for the appropriation of moneys out of the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir;`
  line
  line `(c) for prohibiting the discussion of, or the asking of questions on, any matter which affects the`
  line `discharge of the functions of the Lieutenant Governor in so far as he is required by this Act to act`
  line `in his discretion.`
  line
  line `(2) Until rules are made under sub-section (1), the rules of procedure and standing orders in force`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act, with respect to the Legislative Assembly of the`
  line `existing State of Jammu and Kashmir shall have effect in relation to the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir subject to such modifications and adaptations as may be made`
  line `therein by the Speaker of Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (49704)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 49
  title `Official language or languages of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and language or languages to be used in Legislative Assembly thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49704&sectionno=47&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Legislative Assembly may by`
  line `law adopt any one or more of the languages in use in the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir or`
  line `Hindi as the official language or languages to be used for all or any of the official purposes of the`
  line `Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  line
  line `(2) The business in the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir shall`
  line `be transacted in the official language or languages of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir or in`
  line `Hindi or in English:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Speaker of the Legislative Assembly or person acting as such, as the case may`
  line `be, may permit any member who cannot adequately express himself in any of the languages aforesaid`
  line `to address the Legislative Assembly in his mother tongue.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (49645)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 50
  title `Language to be used for Acts, Bills, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49645&sectionno=48&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 47,`
  line `until Parliament by law otherwise provides, the authoritative texts--`
  line
  line `(a) of all Bills to be introduced or amendments thereto to be moved in the Legislative`
  line Assembly,
  line
  line `(b) of all Acts passed by the Legislative Assembly, and`
  line
  line `(c) of all orders, rules, regulations and bye-laws issued under any law made by the Legislative`
  line Assembly,
  line
  line `shall be in the English language:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Legislative Assembly has prescribed any language other than the English`
  line `language for use in Bills introduced in, or Acts passed by, the Legislative Assembly or in any order,`
  line `rule, regulation or bye-law issued under any law made by the Legislative Assembly of the Union`
  line `territory of Jammu and Kashmir, a translation of the same in the English language published under the`
  line `authority of the Lieutenant Governor in the Official Gazette shall be deemed to be the authoritative`
  line `text thereof in the English language.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (49646)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 51
  title `Restriction on discussion in the Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49646&sectionno=49&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `No discussion shall take place in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly with respect to the conduct of any judge of the Supreme Court or of a High`
  line `Court in the discharge of his duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (49647)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 52
  title `Courts not to inquire into proceedings of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49647&sectionno=50&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The validity of any`
  line `proceedings in the Legislative Assembly shall not be called in question on the ground of any alleged`
  line `irregularity of procedure.`
  line
  line `(2) No officer or member of the Legislative Assembly in whom powers are vested by or under this`
  line `Act for regulating procedure or the conduct of business, or for maintaining order in the Legislative`
  line `Assembly shall be subject to the jurisdiction of any court in respect of the exercise by him of those`
  line powers.
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (49648)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 53
  title `Secretariat of the Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49648&sectionno=51&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Legislative Assembly shall have a`
  line `separate secretariat staff.`
  line
  line `(2) The Legislative Assembly may by law regulate the recruitment, and the conditions of service of`
  line `persons appointed, to the secretarial staff of the Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `(3) Until provision is made by the Legislative Assembly under sub-section (2), the Lieutenant`
  line `Governor may, after consultation with the Speaker of the Legislative Assembly make rules regulating`
  line `the recruitment, and the conditions of service of persons appointed, to the secretarial staff of the`
  line `Assembly and any rules so made shall have effect subject to the provisions of any law made under the`
  line `said sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (49705)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 54
  title `Power of Lieutenant Governor to promulgate Ordinances during recess of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49705&sectionno=52&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `If at any time, except when the Legislative Assembly is in session, the Lieutenant`
  line `Governor thereof is satisfied that circumstances exist which render it necessary for him to take`
  line `immediate action, he may promulgate such Ordinances as the circumstances appear to him to require:`
  line
  line `Provided that the power of making an Ordinance under this section shall extend only to those`
  line `matters with respect to which the Legislative Assembly has power to make laws.`
  line
  line `(2) An Ordinance promulgated under this section shall have the same force and effect as an Act of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly assented by the Lieutenant Governor but every such Ordinance--`
  line
  line `(a) Shall be laid before the Legislative Assembly and shall cease to operate at the expiration of`
  line `six weeks from the re-assembly of the Legislative Assembly, or if before the expiration of that`
  line `period a resolution disapproving it is passed by the Legislative Assembly; and`
  line
  line `(b) May be withdrawn at any time by the Lieutenant Governor.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (49650)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 55
  title `Council of Ministers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49650&sectionno=53&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Council of Ministers consisting of not more than`
  line `ten per cent. of the total number of members in the Legislative Assembly, with the Chief Minister at`
  line `the head to aid and advise the Lieutenant Governor in the exercise of his functions in relation to`
  line `matters with respect to which the Legislative Assembly has power to make laws except in so far as he`
  line `is required by or under this Act to act in his discretion or by or under any law to exercise any judicial`
  line `or quasi-judicial functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The Lieutenant Governor shall, in the exercise of his functions, act in his discretion in a matter:`
  line
  line `(i) which falls outside the purview of the powers conferred on the Legislative Assembly; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in which he is required by or under any law to act in his discretion or to exercise any`
  line `judicial functions; or`
  line
  line `(iii) related to All India Services and Anti Corruption Bureau:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any question arises whether any matter is or is not a matter as respects which`
  line `the Lieutenant Governor is by or under this Act required to act in his discretion, the decision of the`
  line `Lieutenant Governor in his discretion shall be final, and the validity of anything done by the`
  line `Lieutenant Governor shall not be called in question on the ground that he ought or ought not to`
  line `have acted in his discretion.`
  line
  line `(3) The question whether any, and if so what, advice was tendered by Ministers to the Lieutenant`
  line `Governor shall not be inquired into in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (49651)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 56
  title `Other provisions as to Ministers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49651&sectionno=54&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Minister shall be appointed by the`
  line `Lieutenant Governor and the other Ministers shall be appointed by the Lieutenant Governor on the`
  line `advice of the Chief Minister.`
  line
  line `(2) The Ministers shall hold office during the pleasure of the Lieutenant Governor.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council of Ministers shall be collectively responsible to the Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `(4) Before a Minister enters upon his office, the Lieutenant Governor shall administer to him the`
  line `oaths of office and of secrecy according to the forms set out for the purpose in the Fourth Schedule to`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) A Minister who for any period of six consecutive months is not a member of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly shall at the expiration of that period cease to be a Minister.`
  line
  line `(6) The salaries and allowances of Ministers shall be such as the Legislative Assembly may from`
  line `time to time by law determine, and until the Legislative Assembly so determines, shall be determined`
  line `by the Lieutenant Governor.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (49652)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 57
  title `Conduct of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49652&sectionno=55&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1)The Lieutenant Governor shall make rules on the advice of the`
  line `Council of Ministers---`
  line
  line `(a) for the allocation of business to the Ministers; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the more convenient transaction of business with the Ministers including the procedure`
  line `to be adopted in case of a difference of opinion between the Lieutenant Governor and the Council`
  line `of Ministers or a Minister.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, all executive action of the Lieutenant Governor,`
  line `whether taken on the advice of his Ministers or otherwise, shall be expressed to be taken in the name`
  line `of the Lieutenant Governor.`
  line
  line `(3) Orders and other instruments made and executed in the name of the Lieutenant Governor, shall`
  line `be authenticated in such manner as may be specified in rules to be made by the Lieutenant Governor`
  line `on the advice of Council of Ministers, and the validity of an order or instrument which is so`
  line `authenticated shall not be called in question on the ground that it is not an order or instrument made or`
  line `executed by the Lieutenant Governor.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (49706)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 58
  title `Duties of Chief Minister as respects the furnishing of information to the Lieutenant Governor, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49706&sectionno=56&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the Chief Minister—`
  line
  line `(a) to communicate to the Lieutenant Governor all decisions of the Council of Ministers`
  line `relating to the administration of the affairs of the Union territory and proposals for legislation;`
  line
  line `(b) to furnish such information relating to the administration of the affairs of the Union territory`
  line `and proposals for legislation as Lieutenant Governor may call for.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (49654)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 59
  title `Abolition of Legislative Council of the State of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49654&sectionno=57&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any law, document, judgment, ordinance, rule,`
  line `regulation or notification, on and from the appointed day, the Legislative Council of the existing State`
  line `of Jammu and Kashmir shall stand abolished.`
  line
  line `(2) On the abolition of the Legislative Council, every member thereof shall cease to be such`
  line member.
  line
  line `(3) All Bills pending in the Legislative Council immediately before the appointed day shall lapse`
  line `on the abolition of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (49655)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 60
  title `Appointment of Lieutenant Governor of Union territory of Ladakh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49655&sectionno=58&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Union`
  line `territory of Ladakh will be administered by the President acting, to such extent as he thinks fit,`
  line `through a Lieutenant Governor to be appointed by him under article 239.`
  line
  line `(2) The President may make regulations for the peace, progress and good government of the`
  line `Union territory of Ladakh under article 240 of the Constitution of India.`
  line
  line `(3) Any regulation so made may repeal or amend any Act made by Parliament or any other law`
  line `which is for the time being applicable to the Union territory of Ladakh and, when promulgated by the`
  line `President, shall have the same force and effect as an Act of Parliament which applies to the Union`
  line `territory of Ladakh.`
  line
  line `(4) The Lieutenant Governor shall be assisted by advisor(s) to be appointed by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (49656)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 61
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49656&sectionno=59&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `In this Part, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) “associate member” means a member associated with the Delimitation Commission under`
  line `section 60;`
  line
  line `(b) “Delimitation Commission” means the Delimitation Commission to be constituted under`
  line `section 3 of the Delimitation Act, 2002 (33 of 2002); and thereafter by any law made by the`
  line Parliament.
  line
  line `(c) “Election Commission” means the Election Commission appointed by the President under`
  line `article 324 of the Constitution of India;`
  line
  line `(d) “latest census figures” mean the census figures ascertained at the latest census of which the`
  line `finally published figures are available;`
  line
  line `(e) “Parliamentary Constituency” means a constituency provided by law for the purpose of`
  line `elections to the House of the People from Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union`
  line `territory of Ladakh.`
  line
  line `(f) “Assembly Constituency” means a constituency provided by law for the purpose of elections`
  line `to the Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (49657)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 62
  title `Delimitation of constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49657&sectionno=60&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to sub-sections (3) of section 14 of`
  line `this Act, the number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir`
  line `shall be increased from 107 to 114, and delimitation of the constituencies may be determined by the`
  line `Election Commission in the manner hereinafter provided--`
  line
  line `(a) the number of seats to be reserved for the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly, having regard to the relevant provisions of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) the assembly constituencies into which the Union territory shall be divided, the extent of`
  line `each of such constituencies and in which of them seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled Castes`
  line `or for the Scheduled Tribes; and`
  line
  line `(c) the adjustments in the boundaries and description of the extent of the parliamentary`
  line `constituencies in each Union territory that may be necessary or expedient.`
  line
  line `(2) In determining the matters referred to in clauses (b) and (c) of sub-section (1), the Election`
  line `Commission shall have regard to the following provisions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) all the constituencies shall be single-member constituencies;`
  line
  line `(b) all constituencies shall, as far as practicable, be geographically compact areas, and in`
  line `delimiting them, regard shall be had to physical features, existing boundaries of administrative`
  line `units, facilities of communication and conveniences to the public; and`
  line
  line `(c) constituencies in which seats are reserved for the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled`
  line `Tribes shall, as far as practicable, be located in areas where the proportion of their population to`
  line `the total population is the largest.`
  line
  line `(3) The Election Commission shall, for the purpose of assisting it in the performance of its`
  line `functions under sub-section (1), associate with itself as associate members, four persons as the Central`
  line `Government may by order specify, being persons who are the members of the Legislative Assembly`
  line `of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir or four members of the House of the People`
  line `representing the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir:`
  line
  line `Provided that none of the associate members shall have a right to vote or to sign any decision of`
  line `the Election Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) If, owing to death or resignation, the office of an associate member falls vacant, it shall be`
  line `filled as far as practicable, in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The Election Commission shall--`
  line
  line `(a) publish its proposals for the delimitation of constituencies together with the dissenting`
  line `proposals, if any, of any associate member who desires publication thereof in the Official Gazette`
  line `and in such other manner as the Commission may consider fit, together with a notice inviting`
  line `objections and suggestions in relation to the proposals and specifying a date on or after which the`
  line `proposals will be further considered by it;`
  line
  line `(b) consider all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the date`
  line `so specified; and`
  line
  line `(c) after considering all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before`
  line `the date so specified, determine by one or more orders the delimitation of constituencies and cause`
  line `such order or orders to be published in the Official Gazette, and there upon such publication, the`
  line `order or orders shall have the full force of law and shall not be called in question in any court.`
  line
  line `(6) As soon as may be after such publication, every such order relating to assembly constituencies`
  line `shall be laid before the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (49658)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 63
  title `Power of Election Commission to maintain Delimitation Orders up-to date.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49658&sectionno=61&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Election Commission may by notification in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) correct any printing mistakes in any order made under section 60 or any error arising therein`
  line `from inadvertent slip or omission; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the boundaries or name of any territorial division mentioned in any such order or`
  line `orders is or are altered, make such amendments as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for`
  line `bringing such order up-to-date.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under this section relating to an assembly constituency shall be laid, as soon`
  line `as may be after it is issued, before the Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (49707)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 64
  title `Special provision as to readjustment of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies on the basis of 2011 census.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49707&sectionno=62&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, notwithstanding the publication of`
  line `orders under sub-section (1) of section 10 of the Delimitation Act, 2002 (33 of 2002) or anything`
  line `contained in sub-section (2) or sub-section (4) of the said section, the Delimitation Act, 2002 shall be`
  line `deemed to have been amended as provided below:`
  line
  line `(a) in section 2, in clause (f), the words “but does not include the State of Jammu and Kashmir”`
  line `shall be omitted; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of delimitation of Assembly and Parliamentary Constituencies, the words`
  line `and figures “census held in the year 2001”, wherever occurring, shall be construed as words and`
  line `figures “census held in the year 2011”.`
  line
  line `(2) Readjustment of the constituencies as provided under section 60 in the successor Union`
  line `territory of Jammu and Kashmir into Assembly Constituencies, shall be carried by the Delimitation`
  line `Commission, to be constituted under the Delimitation Act, 2002 (33 of 2002) as amended by this Act,`
  line `and shall take effect from such date as the Central Government may, by order, publish in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `(3) Readjustment of the constituencies as provided under section 11 in the successor Union`
  line `territory of Jammu and Kashmir into Parliamentary Constituencies, shall be carried by the`
  line `Delimitation Commission, to be constituted under the Delimitation Act, 2002 (33 of 2002) as`
  line `amended by this Act, and shall take effect from such date as the Central Government may, by order,`
  line `publish in the Official Gazette, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (49660)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 65
  title `Special provisions as to readjustment of Assembly and Parliamentary Constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49660&sectionno=63&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 59 to 61, until the relevant figures for the first census`
  line `taken after the year 2026 have been published, it shall not be necessary to readjust the division of`
  line `successor Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir into Assembly and Parliamentary Constituencies`
  line `and any reference to the “latest census figures” in this Part shall be construed as a reference to the`
  line `2011 census figures.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (49661)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 66
  title `Procedure as to delimitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49661&sectionno=64&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `The procedure as provided in the law made by Parliament,`
  line `shall apply, in relation to the delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly constituencies under this`
  line `Part as they apply in relation to the delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly constituencies under`
  line `that law.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (49662)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 67
  title `Applicability of Scheduled Castes Order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49662&sectionno=65&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, the Constitution`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir (Scheduled Castes) Order, 1956 [Jammu and Kashmir (Schedule Castes Order,`
  line `1956)], shall stand applied to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of`
  line Ladakh.
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (49663)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 68
  title `Applicability of Scheduled Tribes Order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49663&sectionno=66&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, the Constitution`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir (Scheduled Tribes) Order, 1989, [Jammu and Kashmir (Scheduled Tribes Order,`
  line `1989)] shall stand applied to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of`
  line Ladakh.
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (49664)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 69
  title `Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49664&sectionno=67&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the`
  line `appointed day, all revenues received in the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir by the Government`
  line `of India or the Lieutenant Governor of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir in relation to any`
  line `matter with respect to which the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir`
  line `has power to make laws, and all grants made and all loans advanced to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir from the Consolidated Fund of India and all loans raised by the Government of India or`
  line `the Lieutenant Governor of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir upon the security of the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and all moneys received by the`
  line `Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir in repayment of loans shall form one Consolidated Fund to be`
  line `entitled “the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir”.`
  line
  line `(2) No moneys out of such Consolidated Fund shall be appropriated except in accordance with, and`
  line `for the purposes and in the manner provided in, this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The custody of such Consolidated Fund, the payment of moneys into such Funds, the`
  line `withdrawal of moneys therefrom and all other matters connected with or ancillary to those matters`
  line `shall be regulated by rules made by the Lieutenant Governor.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (49665)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 70
  title `Public Account of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and moneys credited to it.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49665&sectionno=68&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, all other public moneys received by or on behalf of the`
  line `Lieutenant Governor shall be credited to a Public Account entitled “the Public Account of the Union`
  line `territory of Jammu and Kashmir”.`
  line
  line `(2) The custody of public moneys, other than those credited to the Consolidated Fund of the Union`
  line `territory or the Contingency Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, received by or on`
  line `behalf of the Lieutenant Governor, their payment into the Public Accounts of the Union territory of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and the withdrawal of moneys from such account and all other matters connected with or ancillary to the aforesaid matters shall be regulated by rules made by the Lieutenant Governor`
  line `on the advice of Council of Ministers.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (49666)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 71
  title `Contingency Fund of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49666&sectionno=69&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be`
  line `established a Contingency Fund in the nature of an imprest to be entitled “the Contingency Fund of`
  line `the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir”, into which shall be paid from and out of the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir such sums as may, from time to`
  line `time, be determined by law made by the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir; and the said Fund shall be held by the Lieutenant Governor to enable advances to be made`
  line `by him out of such Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) No advances shall be made out of the Contingency Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir except for the purposes of meeting unforeseen expenditure pending authorisation of such`
  line `expenditure by the Legislative Assembly under appropriations made by law.`
  line
  line `(3) The Lieutenant Governor on the advice of the Council of Ministers may make rules regulating`
  line `all matters connected with or ancillary to the custody of, the payment of moneys into, and the`
  line `withdrawal of moneys from, the Contingency Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (49667)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 72
  title `Borrowing upon the security of Consolidated Fund of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49667&sectionno=70&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) The executive power of the Union territory extends to borrowing upon the security of`
  line `the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir within such limits, if any, as`
  line `may, from time to time, be fixed by Legislative Assembly by law and to the giving of guarantees`
  line `within such limits, if any, as may be so fixed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any sums required for the purpose of invoking a guarantee shall be charged on the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (49668)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 73
  title `Form of accounts of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49668&sectionno=71&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `The accounts of the`
  line `Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir shall be kept in such form as the Lieutenant Governor may,`
  line `after obtaining advice of the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, prescribe by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (49669)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 74
  title `Audit reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49669&sectionno=72&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `The reports of the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India relating to the`
  line `accounts of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir for any period subsequent to the date referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 67 shall be submitted to the Lieutenant Governor who shall cause them to be`
  line `laid before the Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (49670)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 75
  title `Provision in case of failure of constitutional machinery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49670&sectionno=73&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `If the President, on receipt of a`
  line `report from the Lieutenant Governor of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, or otherwise, is`
  line satisfied,--
  line
  line `(a) that a situation has arisen in which the administration of the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir cannot be carried on in accordance with the provisions of this Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) that for the proper administration of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir it is necessary`
  line `or expedient so to do,`
  line
  line `the President may, by order, suspend the operation of all or any of the provisions of this Act for such`
  line `period as he thinks fit and make such incidental and consequential provisions as may appear to him to`
  line `be necessary or expedient for administering the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (49671)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 76
  title `Authorisation of expenditure by President.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49671&sectionno=74&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `Where the Legislative Assembly is dissolved,`
  line `or its functioning as such Assembly remains suspended, on account of an order under section 73, it`
  line `shall be competent for the President to authorise, when the House of the People is not in Session,`
  line `expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir pending the`
  line `sanction of such expenditure by Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (49672)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 77
  title `High Court of Jammu and Kashmir to be common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49672&sectionno=75&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the`
  line `appointed day,--`
  line
  line `(a) the High Court of Jammu and Kashmir shall be the common High Court for the Union`
  line `territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh;`
  line
  line `(b) the Judges of the High Court of Jammu and Kashmir for the existing State of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir holding office immediately before the appointed day shall become on that day the Judges`
  line `of the common High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The expenditure in respect of salaries and allowances of the Judges of the common High Court`
  line `shall be allocated amongst the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh`
  line `on the basis of population ratio.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (49673)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 78
  title `Special provision relating to Bar Council and advocates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49673&sectionno=76&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the date referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1) of section 75, in the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961), in section 3, in`
  line `sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) in clause (a), the words "Jammu and Kashmir" shall be deleted.`
  line
  line `(b) after clause (f), the following clause shall be inserted, namely--`
  line
  line `-(g)- for the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh, to`
  line `be known as the Bar Council of Jammu and Kashmir; and Ladakh.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who immediately before the date referred to in sub-section (1) of section 75 is an`
  line `advocate on the roll of the Bar Council of the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir and practising as`
  line `an advocate in the High Court of Jammu and Kashmir, may continue to be members of the Bar`
  line `council of Jammu and Kashmir; and Ladakh, notwithstanding anything contained in the Advocates`
  line `Act, 1961 and the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) The persons other than the advocates who are entitled immediately before the date referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1) of section 75, on and after that date, be recognised as such persons entitled also to`
  line `practise in the common High Court of Jammu and Kashmir or any subordinate court thereof, as the`
  line `case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) The right of audience in the common High Court of Jammu and Kashmir shall be regulated in`
  line `accordance with the like principles as immediately before the date referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 75, are in force with respect to the right of audience in the High Court of Jammu and Kashmir.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (49674)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 79
  title `Practice and procedure in common High Court of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49674&sectionno=77&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Part, the law in force immediately before the date referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 75 with respect to practice and procedure in the High Court of Jammu and Kashmir shall, with`
  line `the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the common High Court of Jammu and Kashmir and`
  line `accordingly, the common High Court of Jammu and Kashmir shall have all such powers to make rules`
  line `and orders with respect to practice and procedure as are immediately before that date exercisable by`
  line `the common High Court of Jammu and Kashmir:`
  line
  line `Provided that any rules or orders which are in force immediately before the date referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 75 with respect to practice and procedure in the High Court of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir shall, until varied or revoked by rules or orders made by the common High Court of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir, apply with the necessary modifications in relation to practice and procedure in the`
  line `common High Court of Jammu and Kashmir as if made by that Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (49675)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 80
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49675&sectionno=78&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Part shall affect the application to the common High Court of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir of any provisions of the Constitution, and this Part shall have effect subject to`
  line `any provision that may be made on or after the date referred to in sub-section (1) of section 75 with`
  line `respect to the common High Court of Jammu and Kashmir by any Legislature or other authority`
  line `having power to make such provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (49676)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 81
  title `Advocate General for Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49676&sectionno=79&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Lieutenant`
  line `Governor shall appoint a person who is qualified to be appointed a Judge of the High Court, to be`
  line `Advocate-General for the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of such Advocate-General to give advice to the Government of such Union`
  line `territory upon such legal matters and to perform such other duties of a legal character, as may from`
  line `time to time be referred or assigned to him by the said Government, and to discharge the functions`
  line `conferred on him by or under the Constitution or any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(3) In the performance of his duties, the Advocate-General shall have the right of audience in all`
  line `courts in the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  line
  line `(4) The Advocate-General shall hold office during the pleasure of the Lieutenant Governor and`
  line `receive such remuneration as the Lieutenant Governor may determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (49677)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 82
  title `Authorisation of expenditure of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49677&sectionno=80&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `The Governor`
  line `of existing State of Jammu and Kashmir may, at any time before the appointed day, authorise such`
  line `expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir as he deems`
  line `necessary for any period not more than six months beginning with the appointed day pending the`
  line `sanction of such expenditure by the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Lieutenant Governor of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir may, after the`
  line `appointed day, authorise such further expenditure as he deems necessary from the Consolidated Fund`
  line `of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir for any period not extending beyond the said period of`
  line `six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (49678)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 83
  title `Authorisation of expenditure of Union territory of Ladakh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49678&sectionno=81&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `The Governor of existing`
  line `State of Jammu and Kashmir may, at any time before the appointed day, authorise such expenditure`
  line `from the Consolidated Fund of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir as he deems necessary for any`
  line `period not more than six months beginning with the appointed day pending the sanction of such`
  line `expenditure by the Parliament:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President may, after the appointed day, authorise such further expenditure as he`
  line `deems necessary from the Consolidated Fund of India for any period not extending beyond the said`
  line `period of six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (49679)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 84
  title `Reports relating to accounts of Jammu and Kashmir State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49679&sectionno=82&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) The reports of the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India referred to in clause (2) of article 151 relating to the accounts of the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir in respect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be submitted to the Lieutenant Governors of the successor Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, and Union territory of Ladakh.`
  line
  line `(2) The Lieutenant Governor of Jammu and Kashmir, thereafter shall cause the reports to be laid`
  line `before the Legislature of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  line
  line `(3) The Lieutenant Governor of Jammu and Kashmir may by order--`
  line
  line `(a) declare any expenditure incurred out of the Consolidated Fund of Jammu and Kashmir on any service in respect of any period prior to the appointed day during the financial year or in respect of any earlier financial year in excess of the amount granted for that service and for that year as disclosed in the reports referred to in sub-section (1) to have been duly authorised; and`
  line
  line `(b) provide for any action to be taken on any matter arising out of the said reports.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (49680)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 85
  title `Distribution of revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49680&sectionno=83&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) The award made by the Fourteenth Finance Commission to the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir shall be apportioned between the successor Union territory of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir; and Union territory of Ladakh by the Central Government on the basis of population ratio and other parameters:`
  line
  line `Provided that on the appointed day, the President shall make a reference to the Union territories Finance Commission to take into account the resources available to the successor Union territories of Ladakh and make separate award for the successor Union territory of Ladakh:`
  line
  line `Provided further that on the appointed day, the President shall make a reference to the Fifteenth Finance Commission to include Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir in its Terms of Reference and make award for the successor Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything in sub-section (1), the Central Government may, having regard to the resources available to the successor Union territory of Ladakh make appropriate grants and also ensure that adequate benefits and incentives in the form of special development package are given to the backward areas of this region.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (49681)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 86
  title `Application of this Part.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49681&sectionno=84&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Part shall apply in relation to the`
  line `apportionment of the assets and liabilities of the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir immediately before the appointed day, between the successor Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and successor Union territory of Ladakh.`
  line
  line `(2) The apportionment of the assets and liabilities of the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir shall be subject to the recommendations of a committee constituted by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The process of apportionment shall be completed within a period of twelve months from the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (49682)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 87
  title `Advisory Committee(s).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49682&sectionno=85&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may by order, establish one or more`
  line `Advisory Committees within a period of 90 days from the appointed day, for the purposes of:`
  line
  line `(a) apportionment of assets, rights and liabilities of the companies and corporations constituted for the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir between Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh;`
  line
  line `(b) issues relating to Continuance of arrangements in regard to generation and supply of electric power and supply of water;`
  line
  line `(c) issues related to Jammu and Kashmir State Financial Corporation;`
  line
  line `(d) issues related to Companies constituted for the existing state of Jammu and Kashmir`
  line `regarding the division of the interests and shares and reconstitution of Board of Directors;`
  line
  line `(e) issues related to facilities in certain State Institutions; and`
  line
  line `(f) issues related to any other matters not covered under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The committees so appointed under sub-section (1) of this section, shall submit their reports within six months to the Lieutenant Governor of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, who shall act on the recommendations of such committees within a period of 30 days from the date of receiving such reports.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (49683)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 88
  title `Temporary provisions as to continuance of certain existing road transport permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49683&sectionno=86&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 88 of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988 (59 of 1988), a permit granted by the State Transport Authority of the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir or any Regional Transport Authority in that State shall, if such permit was, immediately before the appointed day, valid and effective in any area in the transferred territory, be deemed to continue to be valid and effective in that area after that day till its period of validity subject to the provisions of that Act as for the time being in force in that area; and it shall not be necessary for any such permit to be countersigned by the Transport Authority of any of Union territory or any Regional Transport Authority therein for the purpose of validating it for use in such area:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Lieutenant Governor may add to amend or vary the conditions attached to the permit by the Authority by which the permit was granted.`
  line
  line `(2) No tolls, entrance fees or other charges of a like nature shall be levied after the appointed day in respect of any transport vehicle for its operations in any of the successor Union territories under any such permit, if such vehicle was, immediately before that day, exempt from the payment of any such toll, entrance fees or other charges for its operations in the transferred territory:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, after consultation with the Government of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir or the administration of Union territory of Ladakh, as the case may be, authorise the levy of any such toll, entrance fees or other charges, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the provisions of this sub-section shall not be applicable where any such tolls, entrance fees or other charges of a like nature are leviable for the use of any road or bridge which is constructed or developed for commercial purpose by the State Government, an undertaking of the State Government, a joint undertaking in which the State Government is a shareholder or the private sector.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (49684)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 89
  title `Special provision as to income-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49684&sectionno=87&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `Where the assets, rights and liabilities of any body corporate carrying on business are, under the provisions of this Part, transferred to any other bodies corporate which after the transfer carry on the same business, the losses or profits or gains sustained by the body corporate first-mentioned which, but for such transfer, would have been allowed to be`
  line `carried forward and set off in accordance with the provisions of Chapter VI of the Income-tax Act,`
  line `1961 (43 of 1961), shall be apportioned amongst the transferee bodies corporate in accordance with`
  line `the rules to be made by the Central Government in this behalf and, upon such apportionment, the`
  line `share of loss allotted to each transferee body corporate shall be dealt with in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of Chapter VI of the said Act, as if the transferee body corporate had itself sustained such`
  line `loss in a business carried on by it in the years in which those losses were sustained.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (49685)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 90
  title `Provisions relating to All India Services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 2021, s. 3, for sub-sections (2) to (6) (w.e.f. 7-1-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49685&sectionno=88&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this section, the expression "State cadre"`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to the Indian Administrative Service, has the same meaning assigned to it in`
  line `the Indian Administrative Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954 [IAS (cadre) rules, 1954];`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to the Indian Police Service, has the same meaning assigned to it in the Indian`
  line `Police Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954 [IPS (cadre) rules, 1954]; and`
  line
  line `(c) in relation to the Indian Forest Service, has the same meaning assigned to it in the Indian`
  line `Forest Service (Cadre) Rules, 1966 [IFS (cadre) rules, 1954].`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The members of the Indian Administrative Service, Indian Police Service and Indian Forest`
  line `Service for the existing cadre of Jammu and Kashmir, shall be borne and become part of the`
  line `Arunachal Pradesh, Goa, Mizoram and Union territories cadre, and all future allocations of All India`
  line `Services Officers for the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh shall`
  line `be made to Arunachal Pradesh, Goa, Mizoram and Union territories cadge for which necessary`
  line `modifications may be made in corresponding cadre allocation rules by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The officers so borne or allocated on Arunachal Pradesh, Goa, Mizoram and Union territories`
  line `cadre shall function in accordance with the rules framed by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (49686)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 91
  title `Provisions relating to other services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49686&sectionno=89&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who immediately before the`
  line `appointed day is serving on substantive basis in connection with the affairs of the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir shall, on and from that day provisionally continue to serve in connection with the affairs of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh, by general or special order of the Lieutenant Governor of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir:`
  line
  line `Provided that every direction under this sub-section issued after the expiry of a period of one year from the appointed day shall be issued with the consultation of the Government or Administration of the successor Union territories, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be after the appointed day, the Lieutenant Governor of Jammu and Kashmir shall, by general or special order, determine the successor Union territory to which every person referred to in sub-section (1) shall be finally allotted for service, after consideration of option received by seeking option from the employees, and the date with effect from which such allotment shall take effect or be deemed to have taken effect:`
  line
  line `Provided that even after the allocation has been made, Lieutenant Governor of Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir may in order to meet any deficiency in the service, depute officers from one successor Union territory to the other Union territory.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person who is finally allotted under the provisions of sub-section (2) to a successor Union territory shall, if he is not already serving therein, be made available for serving in the successor Union territory from such date as may be agreed upon between the Government of the successor Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Administration of Union territory of Ladakh, or, in default of such agreement, as may be determined by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall have the power to review any of its orders issued under this section`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (49687)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 92
  title `Other provisions relating to services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49687&sectionno=90&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this section or in section 89 shall be deemed to affect, on or after the appointed day, the operation of the provisions of Chapter I of Part XIV of the Constitution in relation to determination of the conditions of service of persons serving in connection with the affairs of the Union or any Union territory:`
  line
  line `Provided that the conditions of service applicable immediately before the appointed day in the case of any person deemed to have been allocated to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir or Union territory of Ladakh under section 89 shall not be varied to his disadvantage except with the previous approval of the Lieutenant Governor.`
  line
  line `(2) All services prior to the appointed day rendered by a person,--`
  line
  line `(a) if he is deemed to have been allocated to any Union territory under section 89, shall be deemed to have been rendered in connection with the affairs of that Union territory;`
  line
  line `(b) if he is deemed to have been allocated to the Union in connection with the administration of the successor Union territory, shall be deemed to have been rendered in connection with the affairs of the Union, for the purposes of the rules regulating his conditions of service.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of section 89 shall not apply in relation to members of any All-India Service.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (49688)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 93
  title `Provisions as to continuance of officers in same post.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49688&sectionno=91&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `Every person who, immediately`
  line `before the appointed day, is holding or discharging the duties of any post or office in connection with`
  line `the affairs of the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir in any area which on that day falls within one`
  line `of the successor Union territory shall continue to hold the same post or office in that successor Union`
  line `territory, and shall be deemed, on and from that day, to have been duly appointed to the post or office`
  line `by the Government of, or other appropriate authority in, that successor Union territory:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent a competent authority, on and from`
  line `the appointed day, from passing in relation to such person any order affecting the continuance in such`
  line `post or office.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (49689)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 94
  title `Provision for employees of Public Sector Undertakings, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49689&sectionno=92&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed`
  line `day, the employees of State Public Sector Undertakings, corporations and other autonomous bodies`
  line `shall continue to function in such undertaking, corporation or autonomous bodies for a period of one`
  line `year and during this period the corporate body concerned shall determine the modalities for`
  line `distributing the personnel between the successor Union territories.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (49690)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 95
  title `Provisions as to State Public Service Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49690&sectionno=93&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Public Service Commission for`
  line `the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir shall, on and from the appointed day, be the Public Service`
  line `Commission for the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  line
  line `(2) The Union Public Service Commission, with the approval of the President, shall serve the`
  line `needs of the Union territory of Ladakh.`
  line
  line `(3) The persons holding office immediately before the appointed day as the Chairman or other`
  line `member of the Public Service Commission for the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir shall, as from`
  line `the appointed day, be the Chairman or, as the case may be, the other member of the Public Service`
  line `Commission for the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  line
  line `(4) Every person who becomes the Chairman or other member of the Public Service Commission`
  line `for the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir on the appointed day under sub-section (3) shall be`
  line `entitled to receive from the Government of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, conditions of`
  line `service not less favourable than those to which he was entitled under the provisions applicable to him.`
  line
  line `(5) The report of the Jammu and Kashmir Public Service Commission as to the work done by the`
  line `Commission in respect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be presented to the Lieutenant`
  line `Governor of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, and the Lieutenant Governor of the Union`
  line `territory of Jammu and Kashmir shall, on receipt of such report, cause a copy thereof together with a`
  line `memorandum explaining as far as possible, as respects the cases, if any, where the advice of the`
  line `Commission was not accepted, the reasons for such non-acceptance to be laid before the Legislature`
  line `of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (49691)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 96
  title `Amendment of section 15 of Act 37 of 1956.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49691&sectionno=94&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in section 15`
  line `of the States Reorganisation Act, 1956, in clause (a), for the words “Jammu and Kashmir” the words`
  line `“Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh” shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (49692)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 97
  title `Territorial extent of laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49692&sectionno=95&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) All Central laws in Table-1 of the Fifth Schedule to this Act,`
  line `on and from the appointed day, shall apply in the manner as provided therein, to the Union territory of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh.`
  line
  line `(2) All other laws in Fifth Schedule, applicable to existing State of Jammu and Kashmir`
  line `immediately before the appointed day, shall apply in the manner as provided therein, to the Union`
  line `territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (49693)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 98
  title `Power to adapt laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49693&sectionno=96&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of facilitating the application in relation to the`
  line `successor Union territories, of any law made before the appointed day, as detailed in Fifth Schedule to`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, before the expiration of one year from that day, by order, make`
  line `such adaptations and modifications of the law, whether by way of repeal or amendment, as may be`
  line `necessary or expedient, and thereupon every such law shall have effect subject to the adaptations and`
  line `modifications so made until altered, repealed or amended by a competent Legislature or other`
  line `competent authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (49694)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 99
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49694&sectionno=97&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has`
  line `been made under section 96 for the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court,`
  line `tribunal or authority, required or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose of facilitating`
  line `its application in relation to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir or Union territory of Ladakh,`
  line `construe the law in such manner, without affecting the substance, as may be necessary or proper in`
  line `regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (49695)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 100
  title `Power to name authorities, etc., for exercising statutory functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49695&sectionno=98&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `The Lieutenant`
  line `Governor, as respects the concerned territory may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the`
  line `authority, officer or person who, on or after the appointed day, shall be competent to exercise such`
  line `functions exercisable under any law in force on that day as may be mentioned in that notification and`
  line `such law shall have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (49696)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 101
  title `Legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49696&sectionno=99&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the existing State of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir is a party to any legal proceedings with respect to any property, rights or`
  line `liabilities subject to apportionment among the successor Union territories under this Act, the Union`
  line `territory of Jammu and Kashmir or the Union territory of Ladakh which succeeds to, or acquires a`
  line `share in, that property or those rights or liabilities by virtue of any provision of this Act shall be`
  line `deemed to be substituted for the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir or added as a party to those`
  line `proceedings, and the proceedings may continue accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (49697)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 102
  title `Transfer of pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49697&sectionno=100&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every proceeding pending immediately before the`
  line `appointed day before a court (other than High Court), tribunal, authority or officer in any area which`
  line `on that day falls within the State of Jammu and Kashmir shall, if it is a proceeding relating exclusively`
  line `to the territory, which as from that day are the territories of any Union territory, stand transferred to`
  line `the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer of that Union territory.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any proceeding should stand transferred under`
  line `sub-section (1), it shall be referred to the common High Court of Jammu and Kashmir and the`
  line `decision of that High Court shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section--`
  line
  line `(a) proceeding includes any suit, case or appeal; and`
  line
  line `(b) corresponding court, tribunal authority or officer in any of Union territory means--`
  line
  line `(i) the court, tribunal, authority or officer in which, or before whom, the proceeding would`
  line `have laid if it had been instituted after the appointed day; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of doubt, such court, tribunal, authority, or officer in that Union territory, as may`
  line `be determined after the appointed day by the Government or administration of that Union`
  line `territory, or the Central Government, as the case may be, or before the appointed day by the`
  line `Government of the existing State of Jammu and Kashmir to be the corresponding court,`
  line `tribunal, authority or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (49698)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 103
  title `Right of pleaders to practise in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49698&sectionno=101&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, is enrolled as a pleader entitled to practise in any subordinate court in the existing State`
  line `of Jammu and Kashmir shall, for a period of one year from that day, continue to be entitled to practise`
  line `in those courts, notwithstanding that the whole or any part of the territories within the jurisdiction of`
  line `those courts has been transferred to any of the Union territories.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (49699)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 104
  title `Effect of provisions of the Act inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49699&sectionno=102&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act`
  line `shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (49700)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 105
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041&sectionId=49700&sectionno=103&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00071_201934_1568889824041
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions`
  line `of this Act, the President may, by order do anything not inconsistent with such provisions which`
  line `appears to him to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of five years from the`
  line `appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
